li>\n  <li>by contacting HMRC and asking them to <a href=\"/reporting-your-tax-code-as-wrong\" title=\"Amend your tax code\">amend your tax code</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong></p>\n\n<p>You donate £100 to charity through Gift Aid &ndash; they claim 20% to make your donation £125. You pay 50% tax so you can personally claim back £37.50 (£125 x 30%).</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/donating-to-charity/donating-straight-from-your-wages-or-pension","slug":"donating-straight-from-your-wages-or-pension","order":3,"title":"Donating straight from your wages or pension","body":"<p>If you pay tax through Pay As You Earn (<abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr>), &lsquo;Payroll Giving&rsquo; lets you reduce the cost to you of making gifts to UK charities. </p>\n\n<p>If your employer, company or personal pension provider runs a Payroll Giving scheme, you simply tell them to make the donation from your wages or pension before taking off any tax. </p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong> </p>\n\n<p>You pay tax at the basic rate of 20% and make a monthly donation of £10. That means you save £2 tax (20% of £10). The actual cost of the donation to you is £8.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>For more help you can contact the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kbroker/hmrc/contactus/search.ladv?raction=view&amp;fl0=__dsid%3A&amp;sm=0&amp;ha=34&amp;as=1&amp;sf=&amp;sp_scope=hmrc&amp;sc=hmrc&amp;nh=10&amp;sr=0&amp;cs=ISO-8859-1&amp;tx1=&amp;tx0=49641\" title=\"HMRC Charities Helpline\">HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) Charities Helpline.</a></p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Employers thinking about setting up a scheme should read the <a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/businesses/giving/payroll-giving.htm\" title=\"Payroll Giving guidance\" rel=\"external\">Payroll Giving guidance</a> on the <abbr title=\"Her Majesty's Revenue