ty.</p>\n\n<h2>How the winners are decided</h2>\n\n<p>Local assessment panels look at all the nominations and decide which ones to send to the National Award Committee. </p>\n\n<p>The committee makes recommendations to the Cabinet Office, which sends a final list to the Queen for her approval.</p>\n\n<p>Winners are announced on June 2 every year.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/queens-award-for-voluntary-service/how-to-make-a-nomination","slug":"how-to-make-a-nomination","order":2,"title":"How to make a nomination","body":"<p>You can nominate a group if you&rsquo;re not part of it. You can make your nomination at any time, and there are notes to help you. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><a href=\"http://qavs.direct.gov.uk\" title=\"Nominate a group for the Queen's Award for Voluntary Service\" rel=\"external\">Nominate a group for the Queen’s Award for Voluntary Service online</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Support for your nomination</h2>\n\n<p>When you nominate a group you also need letters from 2 people who support your nomination.</p>\n\n<p>They can be:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a volunteer with the group</li>\n  <li>someone who benefits from their work</li>\n  <li>someone who is aware of their work</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If one of the supporters falls into any of the above categories, the other must be completely independent of the group.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>To make sure your group is considered for an award the year after you nominate them, submit your nomination by 30 September.</p>\n</div>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Charities, volunteering and honours","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship%2Fcharities-honours.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Nominating someone for an honour, setting up a charity and how to volunteer","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=citizenship%2Fcharities-honours","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk