fit in kind, they may be classed as an <a href=\"/employment-status/employee\" title=\"employment status: employee\">employee</a> or <a href=\"/employment-status/worker\" title=\"Employment status: worker\">worker</a>, rather than a volunteer. This includes any promise of a contract or paid work in the future.</p>\n\n<p>Being classed as an employee or worker gives them certain employment rights, like getting the <a href=\"/your-right-to-minimum-wage/\" title=\"the minimum wage: who is entitled to it and how much it is\">minimum wage</a>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example 1</strong></p>\n\n<p>Ellie volunteers at a company to get some work experience. She&rsquo;s given travel expenses even though she walks to work. This is payment, rather than out-of-pocket expenses, so she must be paid at least the minimum wage.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example 2</strong></p>\n\n<p>Joe is an unpaid intern at a record company, but he&rsquo;s given free CDs as a perk. The CDs are &lsquo;benefits in kind&rsquo;. They mean he must be paid at least the minimum wage.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example 3</strong></p>\n\n<p>Amanda is a unpaid intern at a design company. She&rsquo;s been promised that she&rsquo;ll be taken on as an employee after 3 months. This counts as a reward, so she must be paid at least the minimum wage for the whole time she spends at the company.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/volunteering/when-people-can-volunteer","slug":"when-people-can-volunteer","order":3,"title":"When people can volunteer","body":"<h2>Age limits</h2>\n\n<p>There’s no upper age limit on volunteering. However, some organisations’ insurance policies don’t cover people under 16 or over a certain age (usually 80). </p>\n\n<p>Under 14s <strong>can&rsquo;t</strong> work for a profit-making organisation, even if they’re not paid. </p>\n\n<p>Some local councils have bylaws with extra rules about the work young people can do. For example, they may see a charity shop as a profit-making organisation and not let young people volunteer there.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>People aged 50+ can find volunteering opportunities with the <a href=\"http://www.csv-rsvp.org.uk/site/home.htm\" title=\"Retired and Senior Volunteering Programme\" rel=\"external\">Retired and Senior Volunteering Programme.</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>People on benefits</h2>\n\n<p>People can volunteer and claim benefits if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the only money they get from volunteering is to cover expenses, like travel costs</li>\n  <li>they continue to meet the conditions of the benefit they get</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dwp.gov.uk/docs/dwp1023.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Guide to volunteering while on benefits' (PDF, 372KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guide to volunteering while on benefits’ (PDF, 372KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Criminal records</h2>\n\n<p>People with criminal records can volunteer but depending on the offence they may not be able to volunteer in certain roles. They might need a <a href=\"/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check\" title=\"get a Criminal Records Bureau check\">criminal records check</a> if they want to volunteer with children or vulnerable adults. </p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/volunteering/find-volunteer-placements","slug":"find-volunteer-placements","order":4,"title":"Find volunteer placements","body":"<p>You can search for volunteer placements:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.do-it.org.uk/\" title=\"Do-it\">Do-it</a> website</li>\n  <li>in your local community through <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.csv.org.uk/?display=volunteering/\" title=\"Community Service Volunteers\">Community Service Volunteers</a> and by checking local noticeboards (eg, in your library) or newspapers </li>\n  <li>on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.vso.org.uk/\" title=\"VSO\">VSO</a> website, if you are looking for overseas placements </li>\n  <li>by contacting your <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.volunteering.org.uk/finder\" title=\"find your local volunteer centre\">local Volunteer Centre</a></li>\n  <li>on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.reachskills.org.uk/\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> website, if you have skills you&rsquo;d like to volunteer - like accountancy, marketing, law, management, mentoring or IT</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Young people</h2>\n\n<p>You can also register for volunteer placements through:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://nationalcitizenservice.direct.gov.uk/\" title=\"National Citizen Service\">National Citizen Service website</a>, if you&rsquo;re 16 to 17 years old in England or Wales, or 15 to 16  in Northern Ireland.</li>\n  <li>the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ics-uk.org.uk/about/\" title=\"International Citizen Service\">International Citizen Service website</a>, if you&rsquo;d like to volunteer abroad and are between 18 and 25</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Help from Jobcentre Plus</h2>\n\n<p>Jobcentre Plus runs a volunteering programme called Work Together, as well as work experience schemes and work trials for unemployed people looking for work - read more about <a href=\"/moving-from-benefits-to-work/work-experience-and-volunteering\" title=\"Jobcentre Plus help for people looking for volunteering or work experience\">Jobcentre Plus help for individuals</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Jobcentre Plus also runs volunteering and employment <a href=\"/jobcentre-plus-help-for-recruiters/other-employment-schemes\" title=\"Jobcentre Plus help for recruiters\">schemes for recruiters</a>. </p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Charities, volunteering and honours","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/citizenship%2Fcharities-honours.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Nominating someone for an honour, setting up a charity and how to volunteer","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.u